The paper proposes a new framework for Network Representation Learning (NRL) that aims to capture both local and global topological information of a network. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to machine learning and data mining, such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category as it directly relates to the study of networks and their properties.
